## Design Principles

### 1. Generous Whitespace
Let content breathe. Premium products use space liberally.

```typescript
// ✅ Hero sections
<section className="py-24 md:py-32">

// ✅ Content sections  
<section className="py-16 md:py-24">
```

### 2. Professional Restraint
Blue accents, not blue overload. One primary CTA per section.

```typescript
// ✅ Single primary action
<div className="flex gap-4">
  <Button>Get Started</Button>  {/* Primary */}
  <Button variant="outline">Learn More</Button>  {/* Secondary */}
</div>

// ❌ Multiple primary buttons
<div className="flex gap-4">
  <Button>Get Started</Button>
  <Button>Book Demo</Button>  {/* Competing CTAs */}
</div>
```

### 3. Trust Signals
Enterprise logos, security badges, compliance certifications.

```typescript
// ✅ Client logos section
<section className="border-y py-12">
  <p className="text-center text-muted-foreground mb-8">
    Trusted by leading law firms
  </p>
  <LogoCarousel logos={clientLogos} />
</section>
```

### 4. Clear Hierarchy
Guide users through content with visual weight.

```typescript
// ✅ Clear hierarchy
<div>
  <span className="text-sm text-primary font-medium">FEATURES</span>
  <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold mt-2">Powerful AI Tools</h2>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-4">Description...</p>
</div>
```

### 5. Accessibility (WCAG AA)

- Contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text
- Focus indicators on all interactive elements
- Semantic HTML structure

```typescript
// ✅ Accessible focus states
<Button className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:ring-offset-2">

// ✅ Semantic structure
<main>
  <section aria-labelledby="features-heading">
    <h2 id="features-heading">Features</h2>
  </section>
</main>
```

